  },
  "comments": "<p>UV activity:<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/64f225583b10a.png\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/64f225583b10a.png\" alt=\"\"></a><br>© gyoschak</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>UV activity (2004, P#118a):</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668f8b8a43ec.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668f8b8a43ec.jpg\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668f8bc7b761.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668f8bc7b761.jpg\"></a></p><p>© Kiet Tran</p><p><br>The banknote contains a security strip with the inscription \"5 ГРН\" with the national emblem<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/65229ed9b1abd.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/65229ed9b1abd.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br>@ ByRussia45<br>The banknote contains a see-through register<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/65229f0436f80.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/65229f0436f80.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br>@ ByRussia45<br><br>Volodymyr Semenovych Stelmakh was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2000 until 2002 and from 2004 until 2010<br>Serhiy Leonidovych Tihipko was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2002 until 2004<br>Serhiy Hennadiiovych Arbuzov was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2010 until 2012<br>Ihor Viacheslavovych Sorkin was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2013 until 2014<br>Valeriya Oleksiivna Hontareva was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2014 until May 11, 2017<br><br>[b][Donetsk People's Republic Seal/b]<br>Holographic stamp with double-headed eagle and inscription \"Donetsk People's Republic\" used in areas of the self-proclaimed terrorist organization \"Donetsk People's Republic\" in 2014.<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/650ce4883ec0b.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/650ce4883ec0b.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></p>",
